<h4><a href="https://bugs.open-xchange.com/show_bug.cgi?id=53790" rel="nofollow">53790</a> Problem with executing SQL: Deadlock found when trying to get lock</h4>

<p>Possible dead lock situation through concurrent context create operations that imply to add data to “contextAttribute” table in context-associated payload database.This has been solved by adding retry strategy with exponential back-off and added optional lock to ‘contextAttribute’ table to ultimately serialize concurrent write operations. Whether the lock is supposed to be acquired is controlled through newly introduced “LOCK_ON_WRITE_CONTEXT_INTO_PAYLOAD_DB” property in file ‘hosting.properties’.  Default is “false”.</p>

<h4><a href="https://bugs.open-xchange.com/show_bug.cgi?id=53521" rel="nofollow">53521</a> Japanese translation for “Save to Drive” has superfluous letters “()”</h4>

